I frequent this branch because of its convenient downtown location. But they need more tellers!

The ATM would not take my deposit so I had to go inside and they had one teller. On other occasions there has only been one or two tellers. Customer service is not very good either.







Tons of customers in line + Only 2 tellers at the windows + more than 5 employees sitting behind desks = bad customer service







Consistently I find that the customer service at this location is really weak. Plus, it closes at 5pm.







Convenient area off of Castro. There are two ATMs on the outside which are easily accessible. Parking an be a little tricky especially during busy hours when Castro is hopping. Still my go to banking center.







Just came in to get a temp card since I lost my wallet this weekend and Jonathan was such great help. He was really friendly and clearly knew what he was doing.







This branch closes before 5pm. I arrived at 4:57pm asking and pleading, to make a fast deposit but clearly it wasn't early enough. Take your money elsewhere, BoA is corrupt enough before this crap where it's not worth it having to deal with ID theft too, especially when BoA just doesn't care







If I could give this location 0 stars I would. It is really frustrating that EVERY time I come into this location there is a line of over 15 people! This is unacceptable! There are always people wandering around staring at the customers in line but I don't know why they can't get behind the counter and help out! This needs to get corrected. When people ask the BofA reps for help they are not knowledgeable and are rude. This is putting a BAD rap on the bank!







This review is only for the health and safety of the employees and customers.  The smell in this bank (musty) suggests an unhealthy environment.  Not sure if it's mold, or something else, but I actually felt ill while conducting a transaction. I hope it's nothing.







I've been to this bank to make deposits for personal and business accounts. To be fair, I haven't used any other services (such as talking to a personal banker). However, every time I come to the bank, there is only one or two tellers working. At most I've seen there are three tellers. I expect there to be more when it's a Monday/Friday or beginning of the month. There is an awful smell there too. It might be the air conditioning. All in all, expect to be there for a while on a quick transaction. The reason for two stars is for the service you do get when you are seen. The staff seems friendly.







The closing time of this bank has changed from being 6pm M to F. It is now closing at 5pm on M-Th and only open until 6pm on Friday. Super annoying. Good luck if you actually have a full time job and you want to bank with them. Drove all the way here today to find a little "correction" on their time open changing it from 6 PM to 5 PM. There were at least 4 other customers who also came there at the same time who were equally irate. Thanks a lot BofA. Looks like you really don't care about our business.







This branch is the only reason I stopped banking with BOA. At 5:45pm, I came in with lots of cash to deposit for my business,  there was a long line for the personal banking so like usual I went to the business banking line. I stood there, a banker saw me and approached me. I thought she would help me but she simply said there's no business banking at the moment. Seriously? You have a business banking line, you open til 6pm, businesses can complete their transactions at personal line but not business line? Sorry this is my last draw. I will wait til my last vendor is paid and bring my business to Wells Fargo, down the street.







All ATM machines were down when we went there May 2, 2015. There was an event and they closed down castro street. It sucks that you can't get money.







I am not sure why people would give this branch such a bad review. This was my first bank visit in the US, and I was impressed with the good experience. 

The banker attending to me, Kate Thok Mao, ensured that she explained all details, asked questions and so did help me out with making sure that I understood everything and left with no doubt in mind. 

I would say that it is a very good branch, and the employees over there strive to make it a good smooth experience for their customers.







I really like this branch. ..this is the location that is closest to where i live, and i could even walk here, so it has become my go-to location for all my banking needs....







Very bad experience took so long  time to deposited some body of my they live out of state they were ask my I'd to deposited the money in there account 
Very rode staff im not there service







Last summer in August I learned that Bank of America was being fined $16.65 billion dollars for selling "toxic" mortgages. Considering my fairly good experience with the bank, hearing that was somewhat of a shock. Since I am a man of ethics and I do not plan to lend my money to a bank that plays dirty games, I decided that I would not longer associate myself with Bank of America. The fact it broke the record with the largest settlement in history in U.S. corporate history is an indicator that Bank of America engaged in criminal financial behavior that I find deplorable. I resorted to decide to walk away from Bank of America today after a 6-year relationship. I walked in the bank, spoke to one of the employees and then I went to a teller who gave me what was left in my accounts. Nobody asked me if there was anything they could have done to keep me as a customer or why I decided to close the account, a clear indication that Bank of America has absolutely no interest in dealing with customers on a personal level. All they care for is your money and you are one in a million. This is disgusting and it's disgusting to think that employees are probably trained not to care. I closed my account ... what are you waiting for?







I remember why I left Bank of America, this branch confirms the bad customer service, robot tellers and overall bad vibe.







WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE EVER.   
 
I went in with my aunt who needed a verification letter for a loan on a house she was purchasing but the lady said "we don't do that".  Really???  This must be your first day on the job because every bank provides this letter upon request.  After a colleague of hers told her that she is allowed to issue the letter, she asked my aunt if she would like to display a 3, 6, or 9 month average balance on the letter, I asked if her (old) Chinese female colleague can help translate the request since I didn't know how to say "average" in the language.  The exact translation was, "Do you want 3, 6 or 9".  WTF???!!!  3, 6, or 9 what???  This lady obviously didn't want to help.  Who would know what the eff you're asking if you don't ask a complete question???  The day before, she actually HANDWRITTEN a "verification letter".  What bank professional hand writes a verification letter???!!!  What a JOKE!  She told my aunt that day that it was the best she can do.  Well, if  she is so incompetent then she needs to be fired.







Not very happy with this branch. Great location, however bad service... Tellers are nice, which is what made me come here and stay here for the few weeks. With this experience i decided to introduce my friend for a business account... NOT a good experince. In fact, the business banker had no clue what he was doing and at last opened a business credit card for a friend WITHOUT his permission... Eventually bank of america copr. Closed the account and the banker had recieved a notice... BUT not something you would want on your credit and record. Go elsewhere if you can.







I come to this bank only if me and the family are going to eat in Mountain View. I come to withdraw cash as well as find old coins or paper money like I do at other banks (based on my reviews). It does take longer inside this bank than the Vallco branch due to the fact that the tellers are taking their time to go through each transaction. But, I always leave this bank with a smile if I find some old  paper money and coins. I will always be loyal to Bank of America. But, in my opinion this bank as well as the Bank of America on Stevens Creek Boulevard in Cupertino reigns supreme out of all the banks in Silicon Valley.







            Bank of America
        






