        2/7/2015
    

Last summer in August I learned that Bank of America was being fined $16.65 billion dollars for selling "toxic" mortgages. Considering my fairly good experience with the bank, hearing that was somewhat of a shock. Since I am a man of ethics and I do not plan to lend my money to a bank that plays dirty games, I decided that I would not longer associate myself with Bank of America. The fact it broke the record with the largest settlement in history in U.S. corporate history is an indicator that Bank of America engaged in criminal financial behavior that I find deplorable. I resorted to decide to walk away from Bank of America today after a 6-year relationship. I walked in the bank, spoke to one of the employees and then I went to a teller who gave me what was left in my accounts. Nobody asked me if there was anything they could have done to keep me as a customer or why I decided to close the account, a clear indication that Bank of America has absolutely no interest in dealing with customers on a personal level. All they care for is your money and you are one in a million. This is disgusting and it's disgusting to think that employees are probably trained not to care. I closed my account ... what are you waiting for?




