        11/17/2012
    

WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE EVER.    I went in with my aunt who needed a verification letter for a loan on a house she was purchasing but the lady said "we don't do that".  Really???  This must be your first day on the job because every bank provides this letter upon request.  After a colleague of hers told her that she is allowed to issue the letter, she asked my aunt if she would like to display a 3, 6, or 9 month average balance on the letter, I asked if her (old) Chinese female colleague can help translate the request since I didn't know how to say "average" in the language.  The exact translation was, "Do you want 3, 6 or 9".  WTF???!!!  3, 6, or 9 what???  This lady obviously didn't want to help.  Who would know what the eff you're asking if you don't ask a complete question???  The day before, she actually HANDWRITTEN a "verification letter".  What bank professional hand writes a verification letter???!!!  What a JOKE!  She told my aunt that day that it was the best she can do.  Well, if  she is so incompetent then she needs to be fired.




