10





227 S San Antonio RdLos Altos, CA 94022


        (650) 324-4433
    






This branch is centrally located just off Main Street in Los Altos.  It's easy to find, it has a drive-up ATM (and another around the corner, also outside), I haven't been yet when there's a wait for a teller, and everyone I've encountered here is friendly and helpful.  

I only carry checking and savings accounts with Bank of America due to the fees the bank slaps on all of their accounts and transactions, but I have been very happy with this branch.







This branch is seriously a joke. 15 year satisfied customer in San Francisco city with two mortgages in bay area and it took 4 painful trips to the bank to cancel my accounts with them. The atm are constantly out of order and the bank opens at 9am, closed of the weekends and incompetent employees. Wake up people, we are in silicon valley. Gus was extremely rude and Benjamin, the branch manager made me loose hope in this branch and the Bank. 

If you are looking for customer service, go to Wells Fargo. So refreshing







Last Friday I went into the First Republic branch on San Antonio in Los Altos because I needed a Signature Medallion on a document.  Kim, who apparently is the only person on site who can issue a medallion, was stunningly unhelpful.  Her precise phrase was "we won't  touch this."  This was my fourth trip to First Republic to try to get a medallion.  Every prior trip I was told I was missing a (different) key document.  This time she said that she couldn't touch it because my Dad did not have a bank account with First Republic.   The instructions I received had said I could only get a medallion at a bank where I had an account; no one said anything about where my Dad banked.

So I went across the street to Bank of America.  Teri Watkins met me at the door and asked if I needed help.  After a thorough review of my documents, she gave me the medallion I needed.  And I don't even have an account with BofA.  BofA 10, First Republic 0.  I think it's about time I moved my account.







Sitting here waiting...and waiting. The second day in a row I've been here trying to do a simple addition of a name to my account. I left yesterday after waiting 20 min and then being told it would be another 25 minutes at least to be seen. Still waiting now and was told that it's take 30 min to setup a profile once I am finally seen. There are no other clients in the bank. 

Skip this place. There are plenty of other banks in town that treat you as a valuable client and will work for you as they're supposed to instead of leaving you to rot in their waiting chairs.







Changed type of account without proper notification. Spent hours trying to dispute boa refuses to send any proof or verification docs. Dispute returned as "unable to resolve at this time" Be warned. If you had interest baring account double check it!







Teri Watkins is wonderful, I believe she is the branch manager but not sure of her title.  I have been a BofA customer for years, but over the last 4 years I had become increasing disenchanted with the customer support I was receiving.  I was so unhappy I was investigating what other bank I wanted to open an account with.  I decided to go into the San Antonio Branch because I really didn't want to leave BofA and wanted to give them one last chance. I met Teri Watkins and all of a sudden my experience at BofA became what I expected from BofA.  She easily answered my questions, took care of any of the problems I was having and got on the phone to experts if it was something she wasn't sure of.  I have been going to her for any problems for the last 2 years and she always has a smile on her face and painlessly takes care of any problem or questions I have.







Opened both a checking and a savings account here just today, so I can't speak to many problems yet but will definitely update if I encounter any.  I was very careful to make sure I had no hidden fees, and that I understood all the penalty fees (of which there are many).

The customer service was good.  The guy who I spoke with was professional, patient, and knowledgeable.  The wait time was a little rough though; I waited 15 minutes because there was only one person helping with accounts.

The facilities are terrible.  The building is cheap and falling apart, there was trash on the ground and everything just wreaks of cheapness.  It was a bit unsettling, to be honest, that an institution I'm trusting all my money with looks this broken-down.  I guess it was relatively clean, besides the trash.

As far as a bank goes, this is your usual mega-bank.  I opened an account here because I need to have ATMs all over the place for ease of use.  I expected no interest, and my expectations were met - if you are looking to put your life savings somewhere, this isn't the place.  If you're someone who doesn't have a lot of money and just needs it to be liquid, you'll want a big bank like this.  Comparing apples to apples, BoA doesn't seem any better or worse than the other big ones like Wells Fargo or Citibank.

In sum, this specific location, while cheap-feeling, offered good service with a reasonable wait, and has excellent ATMs.







Wow, where to begin? Is it the fact that you can not reach a human at your branch location without circumventing the automated system endlessly? Upon making a trip into the branch to find a human to speak with I observed rolling eyes and over heard a teller remark maybe you should find another bank to a customer?!? WHAT? As for myself I asked twice for a transfer to be made and after discussing other items I asked for confirmation on the requested transfer and the teller told me it hadn't been made. WHAT?!? What in heavens name were we doing all this time? I understand that times have changed and the way we conduct commerce is different now but have we become so dependent on our technology as to be incapable of performing? It's a sad state of affairs in my opinion.







I have had several problems with Bank of America policies since opening accounts here.
Yesterday I deposited two checks within 3 hours of each other,
one at a teller and the other at an ATM.  The first cleared immediately, the 2nd is on hold for 5 days.  They were both written from a local brokerage account.  When I checked with customer service they told me that THIS IS THEIR POLICY.
Be Warned:  If you are going to need the money, use a teller!







Poor service and no ability to do the right thing for customers.  We needed assistance in closing our home loan, and this branch let us down.  They could not execute a simple cashier's check.  I have gotten better service at used car dealers.  Weak!







            Bank of America
        






