384 San Antonio RdMountain View, CA 94040


        (650) 324-4433
    






Pretty average for a BoA. I've come here a few times because of location and convenience, but the parking situation is really bizarre and the exit is just as weird. It feels very boxed in, and confusing to get out of if you have to return the same direction you came.

The staff is nice but sparse, on a busy day count on having to wait quite a bit if your transaction is outside of ATM-ability because they're so understaffed. Otherwise, everyone is pretty nice, they really could use an update though.







Well...not very nice attitude..and if you wanna use the restroom, you have to go to the gas station next door...I don't have any positive impression to BoA. Now never!







Poor personal training. Don't know anything else then a ATM. ( ATM with hands. ) 
I know you'll believe this because a least on a few occasions they need to talk to a manager to resolve a issue they could solve them selfs.







Long wait, not enough employees, and overall, RUDE people that doesn't value their customers. Shahin is the worst Banker I ever met! She didn't even apologize to me for the excessively long wait and demanded me like I'm not a valued customer. It is unfortunate that this is my local bank but I will definitely try to Avoid this bank as much as I could.







Scene : Saturday 950am PST prime time, 15 people in line, 2 tellers
My GOD, other managers/personal bankers/account personal assistant are watching us in line.  The first photo in yelp pretty much was the "real" scene

Get serious please.







Never went inside the bank at all, but like the fact that you can withdrawal $50 dollar bills from the ATM







Long lines, never more than 2 or 3 tellers, though there are spots for about 7 or so of them? 
It is my local bank, and parking is convenient, so, yay. 
2 stars. All about the lines and lack of employees.







Very rude employees, bunch of kids who have no manners & don't know how to treat people. All BOFA banks now have the thick glass barriers & give you a different feel.







Great service, well kept area and a candy bowl always stocked up.  Keep it up, Bank of America!







I give it a 3 start cause it's my local bank and I know most of the employees and they are really nice. What I don't like is that there are 8 employees in the building by only 2 tellers at the window and really long lines. The parking is great.







I liked this bank it's fast and great customers service. Jason and the teller are great taking care of what I need to get done at this bank.







Bank seems understaffed as there is almost never more than 2 tellers working, despite spaces for 8 or so tellers.  Its banking so it's a necessary evil in this day and age.  While they're ok they could do better!







Came at 3:00 pm on a weekday and the wait for an associate was 30 minutes because there was only one banking associate. Geez. The lady greeting, Carla, said it's faster to wait in line for a teller rather than an associate. So, off to the line I went. They have 11 teller windows, but only two tellers and the line was 8 people deep? Geez. 

Anyway, 2 stars for planning on their part. Gave them an extra star because Carla jumped behind a window to solve my problem. Thanks Carla!







Holy moly, the only reason i personally gotta stop by bank is to exchange for some quarters. I've tried coming in during various timing with a hope that service could be better but nay it's the same no matter when u come in. Darn you laundry!!







I'm not surprised this location has 2 1/2 stars.

Worst customer service imaginable and the branch manager failed to return my call.

I'm done with Bank of America. I closed my accounts and will no longer use BofA's services.







Wow.  And the teller who "helped" me took the money out of the WRONG ACCOUNT to boot.  Really, really slow and poor service.  Unacceptable.

The wait was about 30 minutes -- and I have never waited so long at ANY OTHER BRANCH!!







My experience with them so far has been positive! 
Sometimes the branch can get busy but if you go earlier during the day, it's pretty smooth. 

My only complain(and a major one at that) with BoA is that they changed our credit cards with no way to link payments on the old one to the new one.







Horrible customer service. The lines are always way too long. Hello management! Hire more people. No one seems like they want to help you. They refuse to remove fees for cashing a check and tell me that it's impossible. Lies, another location did it for me a week before. This location is awful. Avoid if possible.







They are always short tellers and it's always at least a 20 minute wait.  I keep saying 9th time's a charm but they are never prepared here.  Enough is enough. If you have the option to go to another branch, do it... In fact, you might as well completely switch accounts to another bank while you're at it.







Slowest service ever. Went in around 1pm on a weekday and there was no line but the teller service was slow. She seemed really annoyed that she needed to help me and she told me to wait, as she filled out some papers at her desk. Can't you do that after I leave? Customer service -1 star. 

Deposited 5 checks and got new checks, and that was an half an hour trip. Should have been 10 minutes at the most! 

When I needed to order checks, I sat down with the girl who helped me, it took her a while because I needed my address changed, and I had to spell "Terrace" for her 5 times. 

At the end, when she asked me to check the spelling, she still spelled it "Terrance." 

Come on now! =T







